editorialSummary.text: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

originalText.text: I actually can’t believe the workers at this location. This has been my worst Starbucks experience. Right away the location was extremely chaotic and loud filled with middle schoolers (not the fault of the Starbucks at all) so I felt bad for the workers but I didn’t anymore when I ordered. The worker taking the order was extremely monotone and looked fed up- okay I understand it’s stressful no problem I brushed it off, but then when my drink came out lighter than I wanted I asked the barista very apologetically and politely to add to it and they replied with the nastiest attitude of sarcasm. If you hate your job so much that you have to talk back to a customer asking you something politely then you should change jobs. Only good thing about the location is that they have wifi, a bathroom and some wall plugs.

originalText.text:
I’m begging the store manager here to step up the game. HIRE COMPETENT PEOPLE. I was here on New Years Day and this guy who’s clearly a newbie made both my orders wrong, the vanilla cold foam came out liquid TWICE, the second time he just shook his head, laughed and gave me my coffee. I was in a huge rush so I just left. Wasted $15 that morning. There’s another skinny guy who’s constantly getting orders wrong and being sassy with customers. The women there are carrying the team honestly.

Please for the love of God, hire people that can make the drink and treat them well. Your workers are tired and miserable and the customers aren’t happy.

originalText.text: I wish I could give this location -0 stars. The customer service here is horrible. The wait time for a coffee is insanely long. They never have seasonal ingredients ever. No pumpkin spice for weeks. The baristas have horrible ghetto attitudes when you ask a question or if the coffee isn’t made right. You have to scream over the loud music so they can hear your order. I dread every time I have to order from this location. I avoid it as much as possible living in this neighborhood. Better off going to 57th and 10 Avenue location.

originalText.text: The worst Starbucks ever!!!!! It truly doesn’t even deserve a star. Cashier is to slow, waited 6 mins to give my order!!! Then waited 15 mins more to get my order and that was wrong!! Completely disappointed. The workers are more interested in having conversations amongst themselves then actually doing there job correctly. To top it off the place was dirty, tables filled with old cups and coffee stains. I was in there for 21 mins and not one worker cleaned the tables! To be honest they shouldn’t be open or they should get new workers!!!! Worst experience ever!!!!!

originalText.text: I’ve been going to Starbucks since 2011 and this was the first time I went to a Starbucks and left better than when I entered. The staff here is superb, they are so personable, kind and deeply helpful. I entered on a seemingly normal day for myself, into a lively cafe of people who were enjoying their experiences. The staff had organized a little event and were sharing samples of creations,that are now some of my personal favorites. Not only did this create an environment of community that is usually devoid in a Starbucks due to it being a chain; but it also made my day. This is by far the best Starbucks location I’ve been to not only in the US but abroad.
